# The Kaini / Bocuma voice — SH-101 architecture, set from the
# community's verified SH-01A recreation sheet and checked against
# the record by harmonic analysis:
#   saw dominant + a touch of pulse + a touch of TWO-octave-down
#   square (osc3 at -24 here) — noise is a bus source in Patina, so
#   add `automate noise / 0.1` in the song. VCF key-follow ~0.7 with
#   a real filter envelope (long decay: every note dims as it
#   sustains). Fast attack, long decay, gentle portamento. The wow
#   and the room are the song's job: tape_wow high, tape_drive some,
#   reverb generous. PLAY AT WRITTEN PITCH (saw carries the note).
waveform 2
osc2_wave 1
osc2_pitch 0
osc2_level 0.25
osc3_wave 1
osc3_pitch -24
osc3_level 0.35
detune 0
sub 0
circuit 0
key_track 0.7
osc_fm 0
sync 0
ring 0
glide 0.03
pulse_width 0.5
attack 0.018
decay 1.0
sustain 0.55
release 0.5
filter_env 1.2
filter_attack 0.005
filter_decay 0.8
filter_sustain 0.55
filter_release 0.5
cutoff 1150
resonance 1.1
drive 1.6
saturation 0.8
hpf 16
